R9700: raise unbalanced-loading timeout for big TP2 models on cold page cache
(40-60 GB FP8/AWQ models read from NVMe; rank skew exceeds upstream's 480s,
killing the slower scheduler rank during load → "model loading unbalanced"
crash before serving. 1800s covers a 62 GB worst case at ~40 MB/s tail).
Was a live-only edit on /data/vG (2026-06-02); captured into the series 2026-06-10.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py b/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py
--- a/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py
@@ -284,7 +284,7 @@


 # Detect stragger ranks in model loading
-UNBALANCED_MODEL_LOADING_TIMEOUT_S = 480  # leave more time for post data processing
+UNBALANCED_MODEL_LOADING_TIMEOUT_S = 1800  # leave more time for post data processing (R9700: big TP2 models on cold page cache skew >480s between ranks)


 logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
